1.title: First Call
1.plot: All relationships start somewhere, and many times it's the first call that matters. We shall see if that is the case with LEAH and JEN. A wrong call can be disastrous if the right words are not used. Lets hope for chemistry between these ladies.

2.title: The Move
2.plot: It's clear that if a friend ask for a favor it is only kind to answer the call of duty, but this episode leaves us to ask what kind of "duty" is being called?

3.title: Leah's Confession
3.plot: At this point it seems the conversation starts to become a little more honest, but sometimes actions speak so much louder than words. It will be interesting to learn what these actions have to say.

4.title: JEN's SECRET
4.plot: COMPLAISANT- The docuseries follows the life, love and struggles of LEAH (previously a seemingly happy housewife), and JEN (who was previously a female escort). Though they came from two completely different lifestyles they quickly built a friendship that turned into so much more. Unfortunately their choice to completely change their lives in search of true love with one another does not come without a string of new and in many ways more severe challenges. Is it drug abuse, hidden secrets, a or very complex disease that stands in their way, and can their love overcome...

5.title: Syncope & Incontinence
5.plot: Now that we have been introduced in detail to the two lovely women that will continue to take us on their journey lets dig a little deeper. In the following episodes we will also give an exact name to all the details of the struggles. Starting with why JEN could be losing control of her bladder, and passing out repeatedly.

6.title: The Cane (Problems with gait)
6.plot: At this point what does JEN do when there is a visible change in her daily life? First and foremost she hopes LEAH will not notice. Unfortunately when she must finally use assistance to do one of the first things we learn in childhood the sleight of hand might not help hide her struggle. We are again left to wonder if their love is enough to withstand these drastic changes?

7.title: Optic Neuritis
7.plot: What does one do when they lose one of the very important five senses? The only hope is that there is someone close to help even with the simplest activities of the day. Regardless the question is why and how someone could lose their vision randomly?

8.title: The Revelation
8.plot: The time has come for the guessing game. It's clear things are serious with Jen, but without an official diagnosis, all that's left is speculation.

9.title: Fatigue
9.plot: Apparently JEN has become too "lazy" to do any of the daily chores, but how could this be when she always wants to go above and beyond for the love of her life? Maybe it's something far deeper than being too tired to take care of the household. So what could it be?

10.title: Weakness
10.plot: The fact that JEN is lacking the strength to do almost anything does not stop her from wanting to make LEAH happy anyway she can. Though she does not wear the struggles on her sleeve does not mean they aren't there. Like the saying goes "fake it till you make it". Jennifer does this beautifully. It could also be that she is blessed with the most understanding partner, LEAH.

11.title: MS Hug
11.plot: Yes hugs can be one of the most loving beautiful things in the world, but when it's your own internal body painfully embracing itself and sometimes causing dizziness things be very scary . If only Doctors and the general population could understand there might be a cure. All we survivors can do is pray there is a loving partner that can help us distinguish the difference between our inside attacking itself and our outside being gently held. Leah's current focus is calming the fears and whipping the tears. Love and laughter might be the best option even in the darkest ...

12.title: Dysphagia
12.plot: Since LEAH and JEN are still on vacation it's only customary to start the day with a nice breakfast, right? The only problem is that JEN repeatedly starts choking, and is having a hard time swallowing. Regardless, she still wants to make her love happy so she fights through it in hopes that they will have a lovely day. In the back of their minds they are both wondering the cause of this new "episode".

13.title: Tremors
13.plot: Prior to this point JEN has been able to tell herself and LEAH that she can control, or at least has a handle on the changes going on health-wise. Unfortunately her leg shaking uncontrollably cannot be hidden. Things have gotten very serious, and will be hard to just brush under the rug. LEAH will also make sure that doesn't happen.

14.title: The Letter (Diagnosis)
14.plot: The guessing game is now over. At this point the only questions left are will LEAH stay with JEN despite the results, and how strong is their love?

15.title: The Letter (Diagnosis) Cont'd
